        <section class="intro" id="about">
            <h2>Why Cows Are Amazing</h2>
            <p>Cows are intelligent, social animals that have been companions to humans for thousands of years. They form close friendships, hold grudges, and can even be house-trained. On this website, you'll learn all about these incredible animals and why they deserve our respect and protection.</p>
        </section>
        
        <section class="card-container" id="breeds">
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-img">
                    <i class="fas fa-cow"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="card-content">
                    <h3>Holstein</h3>
                    <p>The Holstein is the most common dairy cattle breed, known for its distinctive black and white markings. Holsteins are bred for high milk production and can produce nearly 10,000 kg of milk per year.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-img">
                    <i class="fas fa-cow"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="card-content">
                    <h3>Angus</h3>
                    <p>Angus cattle, originally from Scotland, are a popular beef breed known for their high-quality meat. They are naturally polled (without horns) and solid black or red in color.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-img">
                    <i class="fas fa-cow"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="card-content">
                    <h3>Jersey</h3>
                    <p>Jersey cattle are a smaller dairy breed known for the high butterfat content of their milk. They are light brown in color and have large, dark eyes giving them a gentle appearance.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
        
        <section class="facts" id="facts">
            <h2>Fun Cow Facts</h2>
            <ul class="fact-list">
                <li>Cows have nearly 360-degree panoramic vision.</li>
                <li>They can detect odors up to 6 miles away.</li>
                <li>Cows have best friends and become stressed when separated.</li>
                <li>They spend about 8 hours a day eating and 8 hours chewing cud.</li>
                <li>A cow's heartbeat is between 48 and 84 beats per minute.</li>
                <li>Cows can walk up stairs but not down stairs.</li>
                <li>They have an excellent sense of smell and can detect scents from 6 miles away.</li>
                <li>The average cow produces about 200,000 glasses of milk in her lifetime.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        
